race.comment: The feature of the day now and KELORA (9) gets another chance to shed his bridesmaid tag. He's bumped into some smart ones recently, including Asphalt, Buthelezi and Westbound in his past four outings. Nothing of that ilk in this race and he'll find this much easier. He'll handle the back up and from a good draw, he can end his winning drought. ASTRO WORLD (16) missed narrowly over 1400m at Ascot last time out when behind a smart one in Fast Harry. CJP takes the ride now and while the wide draw is a niggle, she does tend to get back in the run. Can be finishing strongly. SHOWLAS (13) comes here third-up and also comes through the Fast Harry race from behind ASTRO WORLD last time out. She set the tempo there and felt the pinch late. Fitter again now however and will be hard to catch from up front. ALASKALOT (10) comes here third-up and open to further improvement ss he drops in weight. LOVA SESSION (5) is building nicely this campaign and is not to be discounted.
